<i>I may, without fail</i>

484
00:37:26,246 --> 00:37:31,195
Suffer the first vision
that set fire to the stars

485
00:37:33,526 --> 00:37:36,165
(Caitlin) I don't like it, Dylan.

486
00:37:40,006 --> 00:37:43,840
I've another couple of lines in my head
I'm not sure where to put.

487
00:37:43,886 --> 00:37:47,845
- It's not finished, then?
- No, strictly speaking.

488
00:37:49,246 --> 00:37:52,124
Don't write poems for me any more?

489
00:37:52,166 --> 00:37:55,283
(Sighs) It's just a phase.

490
00:37:57,646 --> 00:37:59,716
Come here.

491
00:38:01,206 --> 00:38:04,243
Bring that body back to me.

492
00:38:30,206 --> 00:38:32,276
(Sighs)

493
00:38:36,726 --> 00:38:38,762
(Sighs)

494
00:39:00,366 --> 00:39:01,560
(Loud knocking)

495
00:39:02,806 --> 00:39:04,364
- Oh.
- Now...

496
00:39:04,406 --> 00:39:06,522
Shh!

497
00:39:12,086 --> 00:39:14,441
(Clears throat)

498
00:39:16,686 --> 00:39:19,883
- It's a marriage licence.
- Special one.

499
00:39:19,926 --> 00:39:22,076
- No.
- What?

500
00:39:22,126 --> 00:39:25,004
You can't make me.
What if I can't love you?

501
00:39:25,046 --> 00:39:28,675
- I've been posted, Vera.
- Well, that's a hell of a proposal.

502
00:39:30,166 --> 00:39:32,600
I... love... you.

503
00:39:32,646 --> 00:39:35,001
(Vera) I am not marrying you.

504
00:39:35,046 --> 00:39:39,198
- No. You don't make the decisions any more.
- No.

505
00:39:39,246 --> 00:39:41,157
- Say it. Say it.
- Uh-uh. No.

506
00:39:41,206 --> 00:39:43,401
- Say, "I'll marry you."
- (Laughs) No.

507
00:39:43,446 --> 00:39:46,483
Say it. Say yes. Say yes. Yes!

508
00:39:46,526 --> 00:39:50,280
- Yes! Say yes!
- (Caitlin and Dylan) Yes!

509
00:39:50,326 --> 00:39:53,796
- Say yes!
- Oh, for God's sake, say yes!

510
00:39:57,006 --> 00:39:59,918
My first was Augustus John.

511
00:39:59,966 --> 00:40:02,958
Seduced me when I was 15, the old goat.

512
00:40:03,926 --> 00:40:06,679
It doesn't mean anything, fucking. It's not love.

513
00:40:06,726 --> 00:40:08,956
I get an itch, it's gotta be scratched.

514
00:40:09,006 --> 00:40:11,076
I'd do it myself, only I'm too lazy.

515
00:40:11,126 --> 00:40:14,641
Why bother, when you can get
someone else to do it for you?

516
00:40:14,686 --> 00:40:18,725
- Nothing to do with love, fucking?
- Uh-uh. Nothing.

517
00:40:20,366 --> 00:40:25,520
- Who was your first?
- What?

518
00:40:25,566 --> 00:40:28,558
You don't need to tell me. I know it was Dylan.

519
00:40:30,646 --> 00:40:33,718
We were kids. Tents piled in a beach hut.

520
00:40:33,766 --> 00:40:37,395
- Nice and comfy, then.
- We were children, still innocent.

521
00:40:37,446 --> 00:40:40,279
We are still innocent, me and Dylan.

522
00:40:41,366 --> 00:40:43,926
I only want it as a memory. I don't want it back.

523
00:40:43,966 --> 00:40:45,558
Does William know?

524
00:40:46,806 --> 00:40:50,242
Don't ever tell him.
I can forgive the past, he won't.

525
00:40:54,086 --> 00:40:55,838
The past I can forgive.

526
00:40:59,126 --> 00:41:01,082
You warning me?

527
00:41:13,406 --> 00:41:15,397
(Sighs)

528
00:41:15,446 --> 00:41:19,724
- You love William, don't you?
- You have to love someone these days.

529
00:41:19,766 --> 00:41:22,360
You sure you want to marry him?

530
00:41:25,326 --> 00:41:31,356
I've never had a best friend before.
Here. See if I look like a mermaid?

531
00:41:34,606 --> 00:41:36,801
(Vera laughs)

532
00:41:37,886 --> 00:41:40,195
(Church bell)

533
00:41:41,366 --> 00:41:44,438
We've a couple of cleaners
who'd be pleased to act as witnesses.

534
00:41:44,486 --> 00:41:46,841
They'll be here, they will.

535
00:41:48,846 --> 00:41:51,519
I'm sorry, we've got couples queuing up.

536
00:41:51,566 --> 00:41:54,319
(Dylan coughing) Sorry!

537
00:41:54,366 --> 00:41:57,642
- About bloody time.
- See?

538
00:42:00,526 --> 00:42:03,598
- Look. Bend down, can't you?
- Three guineas that cost.

539
00:42:03,646 --> 00:42:06,763
How many words is that for
a few feathers and a piece of cloth?

540
00:42:06,806 --> 00:42:10,515
- Where did you get three guineas?
- He wrote a cheque. It'll bounce, of course.

541
00:42:10,566 --> 00:42:13,478
You look beautiful!
Tell her she looks beautiful.

542
00:42:13,526 --> 00:42:15,596
She is beautiful. Come on. Let's get married.

543
00:42:15,646 --> 00:42:19,844
- It was Dylan's idea. He chose it.
- You always did have hats.

544
00:42:19,886 --> 00:42:22,081
(# Hums Wedding March)

545
00:42:23,806 --> 00:42:25,637
(# Piano music)

546
00:42:29,606 --> 00:42:32,564
Would you mind awfully?

547
00:42:32,606 --> 00:42:37,760
I'm terribly sorry. Purely for old times' sake.

548
00:42:43,686 --> 00:42:46,041
(Vera laughs)

549
00:42:48,206 --> 00:42:51,118
- Sorry, old chap.
- Call of duty.

550
00:42:51,166 --> 00:42:53,077
Carry on, Sergeant.

551
00:42:57,566 --> 00:43:00,399
Oh, treat me right, can't you?

552
00:43:00,966 --> 00:43:03,161
Oh, no, no! I want to give a toast.

553
00:43:03,206 --> 00:43:05,674
(Caitlin) I'll squeeze the life out of you.

554
00:43:05,726 --> 00:43:06,875
- Yes, after the toast.
- Go on!

555
00:43:06,926 --> 00:43:08,041
You're killing me.

556
00:43:08,086 --> 00:43:11,681
(Welsh accent) Oh, go on, you great
Welsh bastard, or I'll break you in two!

557
00:43:14,646 --> 00:43:17,683
To all the things that really matter.

558
00:43:17,726 --> 00:43:20,001
- And bugger the ones that don't.
- Hear, hear.

559
00:43:20,046 --> 00:43:22,037
- Can you please get down?
- Sing, and I might.

560
00:43:22,086 --> 00:43:23,519
- Oh, God.
- Sing, Dullun!

561
00:43:27,606 --> 00:43:33,875
# Myfanwy boed yr holl o'th fywyd

562
00:43:33,926 --> 00:43:41,606
(Both) # Dan heulwen disglair canol dydd

563
00:43:41,646 --> 00:43:49,519
# Boed i rosyn gwridog iechyd

564
00:43:49,566 --> 00:43:55,755
# I ddawnsio ganmlwydd ar dy rudd #

565
00:43:55,806 --> 00:43:58,479
It's that old heiryth,

566
00:43:59,486 --> 00:44:02,762
that old Welsh thing
they're always banging on about.

567
00:44:02,806 --> 00:44:05,445
(Caitlin) He hates the bloody place, doesn't he?

568
00:44:06,486 --> 00:44:08,204
Who doesn't?

569
00:44:09,366 --> 00:44:11,163
(# Both continue singing)

570
00:44:11,206 --> 00:44:15,165
(Caitlin) But all he wants, see,
he wants back there.

571
00:44:15,886 --> 00:44:17,877
She's no different.

572
00:44:18,886 --> 00:44:22,515
No, you'll never come between them,
not with them being Welsh together.

573
00:44:22,566 --> 00:44:27,515
- Why should I come between them?
- Course, you've always got me.

574
00:44:31,046 --> 00:44:32,718
Perfect.

575
00:44:34,726 --> 00:44:38,196
<i>(William) "For old times' sake."</i>
<i>That's what he said.</i>

576
00:44:38,246 --> 00:44:41,363
- <i>No harm will ever come to you.</i>
- <i>(Vera) He'll always be my friend.</i>

577
00:44:41,406 --> 00:44:45,194
<i>(William) No word of mine will ever hurt you.</i>
<i>(Vera) I can still have friends.</i>

578
00:44:51,886 --> 00:44:54,639
- You're crying.
- (Sighs)

579
00:44:54,686 --> 00:44:57,200
Dreaming, that's all.

580
00:44:57,246 --> 00:44:59,760
- You're shaking.
- It'll pass.

581
00:45:01,326 --> 00:45:05,319
You'll come back to me. I know you will.

582
00:45:07,286 --> 00:45:09,959
Tell me the truth.

583
00:45:10,006 --> 00:45:12,122
You're hurting me.

584
00:45:13,686 --> 00:45:16,519
I want everything to be open between us.

585
00:45:18,046 --> 00:45:21,118
- And fresh and clean.
- Stop it.

586
00:45:21,166 --> 00:45:23,760
You and your friend.

587
00:45:23,806 --> 00:45:25,797
Tell me.

588
00:45:27,486 --> 00:45:30,046
We were kids, William.

589
00:45:30,086 --> 00:45:34,477
We were on a beach
and it happened, once. That's all.

590
00:45:36,886 --> 00:45:38,717
William.

591
00:45:39,926 --> 00:45:42,042
Tell me you love me.

592
00:45:44,166 --> 00:45:46,680
Come back alive and I'll say it.

593
00:45:47,806 --> 00:45:51,765
Come back to me,
I'll say anything you want.

594
00:45:51,806 --> 00:45:54,115
And mean it?

595
00:45:55,126 --> 00:45:57,765
Come back and see.

596
00:46:09,966 --> 00:46:11,365
(# Band plays)

597
00:46:12,646 --> 00:46:19,279
# Drifting and dreaming

598
00:46:20,606 --> 00:46:26,795
# While shadows fall

599
00:46:28,006 --> 00:46:35,242
# Softly at twilight

600
00:46:36,006 --> 00:46:42,559
# I hear you call

601
00:46:43,686 --> 00:46:51,320
# Love's old sweet story

602
00:46:51,366 --> 00:46:57,157
# Told with your eyes

603
00:46:59,086 --> 00:47:07,164
# Drifting and dreaming

604
00:47:07,206 --> 00:47:13,156
# Sweet paradise #

605
00:47:17,646 --> 00:47:20,956
(Speaks Greek)

606
00:47:23,926 --> 00:47:27,805
- Sergeant, get these men off the aircraft, now!
- Everybody off the plane!

607
00:47:27,846 --> 00:47:30,519
<i>(William) "Of course</i>
<i>you told me because I asked.</i>

608
00:47:30,566 --> 00:47:32,636
<i>"I should have bitten out my tongue.</i>

609
00:47:33,646 --> 00:47:37,002
<i>"You're all I love. You're all my need.</i>

610
00:47:38,086 --> 00:47:40,236
<i>"You're what I see in front of me.</i>

611
00:47:40,286 --> 00:47:43,995
<i>" And if I look over my shoulder, there...</i>

612
00:47:44,046 --> 00:47:46,799
<i>"There, I can see your smile.</i>

613
00:47:47,486 --> 00:47:50,603
<i>" All honour I would give up for you.</i>

614
00:47:50,646 --> 00:47:54,036
<i>"I could accept defeat</i>
<i>if you were by my side."</i>

615
00:48:02,206 --> 00:48:04,720
(Speaks Greek)

616
00:48:07,046 --> 00:48:09,435
(Inhales) Vera.

617
00:48:24,366 --> 00:48:25,685
(Retching)

618
00:48:25,726 --> 00:48:29,321
- Do you want me to hold your head?
- Christ, no!

619
00:48:31,486 --> 00:48:33,477
(Sobbing and retching)

620
00:48:38,246 --> 00:48:41,761
(Caitlin) Now you'll get fat
and Dylan won't love you any more.

621
00:48:41,806 --> 00:48:45,924
- (Laughs)
- You're a bitch.

622
00:48:45,966 --> 00:48:49,197
It's the past Dylan loves.

623
00:48:49,246 --> 00:48:51,237
And you.

624
00:48:52,406 --> 00:48:53,600
Doesn't love me at all.

625
00:48:53,646 --> 00:48:56,114
When's William get back?

626
00:48:57,486 --> 00:48:59,477
I keep writing. No word.

627
00:49:01,326 --> 00:49:03,362
Think he's dead?

628
00:49:04,446 --> 00:49:07,279
I'm still getting his pay.

629
00:49:07,326 --> 00:49:09,965
Army wouldn't pay a dead man.

630
00:49:11,486 --> 00:49:14,284
You'll have to stop singing.

631
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:15,998
I'll sing if I want.

632
00:49:16,046 --> 00:49:18,196
(Laughs) They won't let you.

633
00:49:18,246 --> 00:49:20,476
Not pregnant, they won't.

634
00:49:21,366 --> 00:49:24,881
Oh, I can't do this. I can't.

635
00:49:24,926 --> 00:49:26,882
A mother, me? Look at me.

636
00:49:26,926 --> 00:49:29,156
Well, get rid of it, then.

637
00:49:31,086 --> 00:49:33,964
- It's William's.
- Ah.

638
00:49:34,006 --> 00:49:36,395
You love him.

639
00:49:37,366 --> 00:49:41,245
I hate him. Oh, God, I hate him so much.

640
00:49:41,286 --> 00:49:43,595
- Look what he's done to me.
- (Laughs)

641
00:49:43,646 --> 00:49:48,162
Don't laugh. Don't damn well laugh!

642
00:49:49,126 --> 00:49:53,881
- I can't do this alone. I can't.
- I'm here, aren't I?

643
00:49:53,926 --> 00:49:57,043
- Let's go home, Caitlin.
- I don't have a home.

644
00:49:57,086 --> 00:50:00,556
- Wales, Caitlin.
- Are you insane, woman?

645
00:50:00,606 --> 00:50:04,201
- I've got money.
- What, William's pay?

646
00:50:07,126 --> 00:50:10,357
I've savings. Of course I have.

647
00:50:11,366 --> 00:50:13,243
(Screams)

648
00:50:13,286 --> 00:50:15,675
Hold him! Bloody hold him!

649
00:50:15,726 --> 00:50:17,239
(Screams)

650
00:50:18,886 --> 00:50:23,004
- The whole town will hear you!
- Shut your damn mouth!

651
00:50:23,046 --> 00:50:25,196
(Screams)

652
00:50:25,246 --> 00:50:27,999
- You see this here?
- Yes.

653
00:50:29,606 --> 00:50:31,915
(Squeals)

654
00:50:36,166 --> 00:50:39,203
- Give it here.
- (Muffled groaning)

655
00:50:43,886 --> 00:50:45,080
(Screams)

656
00:50:45,126 --> 00:50:47,560
- Don't let go!
- It's only a baby.

657
00:50:47,606 --> 00:50:49,961
You scream if you want to, Vera. You hear me?

658
00:50:50,006 --> 00:50:52,315
(Both screaming)

659
00:50:53,246 --> 00:50:55,919
- (Sawing)
- (Both screaming)

660
00:50:56,886 --> 00:50:58,956
(Screaming fades)

661
00:50:59,846 --> 00:51:02,201
<i>(Vera) "Please write to me."</i>

662
00:51:02,846 --> 00:51:04,325
(Baby cries)

663
00:51:04,366 --> 00:51:07,483
<i>(Vera) "They tell us what to write</i>
<i>to our boys, so we keep your morale up.</i>

664
00:51:07,526 --> 00:51:12,680
<i>"It's our duty. Damn duty, I say.</i>
<i>I'm no heroine, you see.</i>

665
00:51:12,726 --> 00:51:16,196
<i>"I'm fed up to the back teeth of being on my own.</i>
<i>It's not what I married you for.</i>

666
00:51:17,886 --> 00:51:20,036
<i>"Come home.</i>

667
00:51:20,086 --> 00:51:25,285
<i>"I've got something I might want</i>
<i>to say to you. Remember?</i>

668
00:51:25,326 --> 00:51:28,045
<i>"You do remember, don't you?</i>

669
00:51:28,086 --> 00:51:30,680
<i>"Come home. I want to touch you.</i>

670
00:51:30,726 --> 00:51:33,798
<i>"Where the rain fell on your skin.</i>

671
00:51:33,846 --> 00:51:36,235
<i>"Damn you for making me feel this way.</i>

672
00:51:36,286 --> 00:51:38,959
<i>"Damn you to hell and back.</i>

673
00:51:40,326 --> 00:51:42,442
<i>" And back, William.</i>

674
00:51:42,486 --> 00:51:44,442
<i>"And back."</i>

675
00:51:45,126 --> 00:51:47,515
(Gunfire)

676
00:51:54,486 --> 00:51:58,365
Down. Down!

677
00:51:58,406 --> 00:52:00,715
Man down!

678
00:52:00,766 --> 00:52:02,961
(Men shouting)

679
00:52:08,686 --> 00:52:10,324
(Gunfire)

680
00:52:11,406 --> 00:52:13,476
(Soldier) No, sir.

681
00:52:16,046 --> 00:52:18,480
(Gasps)

682
00:52:18,526 --> 00:52:20,801
<i>(Dylan) Forgive us</i>

683
00:52:20,846 --> 00:52:24,316
<i>Forgive us your death</i>
<i>that myselves the believers</i>

684
00:52:24,366 --> 00:52:26,675
<i>May hold it in a great flood</i>

685
00:52:26,726 --> 00:52:29,035
<i>Till the blood shall spurt</i>

686
00:52:29,086 --> 00:52:31,680
<i>And the dust shall sing like a bird</i>

687
00:52:32,920 --> 00:52:37,994
<i>As the grains blow,</i>
<i>as your death grows, through our heart</i>

688
00:52:38,040 --> 00:52:39,189
<i>Crying</i>

689
00:52:39,240 --> 00:52:40,229
<i>Your dying</i>

690
00:52:40,280 --> 00:52:41,269
<i>Cry</i>

691
00:52:41,320 --> 00:52:45,074
<i>Child beyond cockcrow by the fire-dwarfed</i>

692
00:52:45,120 --> 00:52:49,511
<i>Street we chant the flying sea</i>

693
00:52:49,560 --> 00:52:52,028
<i>In the body bereft</i>

694
00:53:08,520 --> 00:53:10,636
Come on. Sleep tight.

695
00:53:14,520 --> 00:53:17,353
- (Child) I'm hungry.
- Shh.

696
00:53:17,400 --> 00:53:19,709
Baby is sleeping.

697
00:53:28,720 --> 00:53:33,157
It's bloody freezing! Bloody Wales!

698
00:53:34,600 --> 00:53:36,955
(Sighs)

699
00:53:37,000 --> 00:53:40,231
When I was little, my da always
used to warm me like this.

700
00:53:40,280 --> 00:53:43,192
- You loved him?
- Adored him.

701
00:53:43,240 --> 00:53:46,516
- I hated mine.
- You didn't hate him. Not hate.

702
00:53:46,560 --> 00:53:48,869
He was loathsome.

703
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:53,277
Pity you're not a man.
If you were a man, I'd fancy you.

704
00:53:53,320 --> 00:53:56,278
(Snorts and laughs)

705
00:53:56,320 --> 00:53:58,197
Don't think I didn't know you were there.

706
00:53:58,240 --> 00:54:00,913
- I didn't.
- I could smell him.

707
00:54:00,960 --> 00:54:04,919
Come here, Dylan. Let Vera smell you,
smell the woman on you.

708
00:54:04,960 --> 00:54:07,428
- Stop it.
- She thinks I should twiddle my thumbs while...

709
00:54:07,480 --> 00:54:11,029
- What? What?
- Don't wake the kids, Dylan.

710
00:54:11,080 --> 00:54:14,038
So where are they, Caitlin, hm?
Where are your little friends?

711
00:54:14,080 --> 00:54:18,596
Come on, boys. Out you come.
Feeding time. (Laughs)

712
00:54:18,640 --> 00:54:21,552
- Ow! She's killing me! Vera!
- (Children crying)

713
00:54:21,600 --> 00:54:23,556
I will kill you! I will!

714
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:25,397
If I catch you at it again, I will!

715
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:28,477
Why don't you see to the kids, Caitlin? Go on.

716
00:54:30,240 --> 00:54:31,229
(Barking)

717
00:54:31,280 --> 00:54:34,192
- Why do you do it?
- I don't do anything.

718
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:39,588
I do it, sleep with other women...

719
00:54:39,640 --> 00:54:42,234
- Hello.
- Morning.

720
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:45,556
...because I'm a poet, and a poet feeds off life.

721
00:54:45,600 --> 00:54:47,750
- (Laughs)
- What?

722
00:54:47,800 --> 00:54:50,155
Pompous sod, aren't you?

723
00:54:50,200 --> 00:54:53,192
I do it because she does it.

724
00:54:53,240 --> 00:54:56,471
She always has. She can't help herself.

725
00:54:56,520 --> 00:54:59,034
It doesn't mean anything to her.

726
00:54:59,080 --> 00:55:02,868
You don't need William. You've got me.

727
00:55:04,040 --> 00:55:06,508
Nothing but you and me with time on our hands

728
00:55:06,560 --> 00:55:09,120
and each other to spend it with.

729
00:55:11,640 --> 00:55:13,596
(Door closes)

730
00:55:13,640 --> 00:55:15,676
(Footsteps)

731
00:55:16,880 --> 00:55:18,916
Hello, Daisy.

732
00:55:23,720 --> 00:55:27,190
Come back with me. Come on.

733
00:55:28,400 --> 00:55:32,632
I'll take you back to a time
when we were safe.

734
00:55:32,680 --> 00:55:37,708
Where no bombs fell from the sky
and no one died, ever.

735
00:55:37,760 --> 00:55:39,990
You can't go back.

736
00:55:42,600 --> 00:55:44,591
We can.

737
00:55:45,680 --> 00:55:48,148
You and me.

738
00:55:48,200 --> 00:55:50,350
It's not real.

739
00:55:51,080 --> 00:55:53,310
It is if we want it to be.

740
00:56:08,160 --> 00:56:10,628
Pity about the poor bloody husband.

741
00:56:10,680 --> 00:56:14,116
Off bleeding for his country
and paying for the fun back home.

742
00:56:17,200 --> 00:56:19,350
Don't mind if I join you, do you?

743
00:56:32,200 --> 00:56:34,270
(Sighs)

744
00:56:44,480 --> 00:56:46,948
(Woman) Room for a small one?

745
00:56:49,600 --> 00:56:53,309
Ooh, wartime luxury.

746
00:57:06,120 --> 00:57:07,678
(Yells)

747
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:10,957
(Woman) You can drop me here.

748
00:57:11,000 --> 00:57:12,831
(Brakes squeal)

749
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:15,313
(Yells)

750
00:57:17,080 --> 00:57:19,799
(Dylan) Cat?
(Woman) That looks nasty.

751
00:57:21,600 --> 00:57:23,989
Catty, Catty. Cat, Cat, Cat.

